South Africa’s Tongaat Hulett on Wednesday said it expects to swing to an interim headline profit of as much as R189 million ($12.37 million) driven by a turnaround at its local operations, sending the sugar producer’s shares higher. Tongaat said headline earnings for the six-months ended September 30 will surge by between 150% to 160%, or to between R158 million  and R189 million, from a loss of R315 million during the same period a year earlier. Subscribe for full access to all our share and unit trust data tools, our award-winning articles, and support quality journalism in the process. You will be redirected to a checkout page.
