A yearly subscription is refundable within 14 days of purchase and includes a 365-day membership. Shares in Tongaat, which processes sugarcane and maize, had risen 5.99% to R8.14 by 0818 GMT. The agriculture and agri-processing company has sold assets, cut jobs and sought an equity raise to boost cash flow amid high debt levels. The company flagged an increase in operating profit of around 70% for the period compared to the R1.3 billion generated a year earlier on the back of a good performance from its sugar operations and progress in its turnaround strategy. However, higher finance costs and a monetary loss arising from hyperinflation in Zimbabwe weighed on operating profit, the company said. Tongaat said total borrowing fell by around R900 million to R10.9 billion from R11.8 billion a year ago. The interim results are expected to be released on December, 11.